cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this benchmark, dataset, or harness, please cite the following technical report (V11 — Second Update, 100,000-patient cohort)."
type: software
title: "Kantesti AI Engine (2.78T) — Blood Test Benchmark V11 (Second Update, 100K Cohort)"
abstract: >-
  A pre-registered, rubric-based clinical validation of the Kantesti AI Engine
  (version 2.78T) on 100,000 anonymised blood test cases drawn from a SQL-backed
  clinical data repository spanning 127 countries and 75+ languages. This is
  the Second Update of the V11 Kantesti Blood Test Benchmark suite, extending
  the original V11 release (15 anonymised cases, proof-of-concept) to a
  population-scale evaluation while preserving the V11 scoring rubric
  byte-for-byte. The engine achieved a composite score of approximately 0.998
  (99.80%) with perfect structural conformance, near-perfect clinical
  conformance, a mean end-to-end response latency of 13.26 seconds, and zero
  hyperdiagnosis false-positives on the trap-case subset. The full evaluation
  harness — including the SQL-driven case loader — is released under the MIT
  licence.
